Let me retrace the code step by step. Original code:

int [] ans = new int[n];

Arrays.fill(ans, l);

sAll -= sk + (n - k)*l; sk -= k * l; Wait, the first line after filling the array with l:

sAll is being reduced by (sk + (n -k)*l). Then sk is reduced by k*l.

Then, there are two loops:

First loop: while sk >0, increment the last elements (starting from the end) until sk is 0. Second loop: while sAll>0, increment the first elements (starting from the beginning) until sAll is 0. Wait, the first loop:

The first loop's code:

while (sk >0) {

    int idx = n-1;

    while (sk>0 && idx >= n -k) {

        ans[idx]++;

        sk--;

        idx--;

    }

}

This loop is trying to distribute the remaining sk by increasing the last k elements (since idx starts at n-1 and goes down to n-k).

Each time, it increments the current element, subtracts 1 from sk, and moves to the previous element (idx--). This continues until sk is 0 or until idx is less than n-k.

The second loop:

while (sAll>0) {

    int idx =0;

    while (sAll>0 && idx < n -k) {

        ans[idx]++;

        sAll--;

        idx++;

    }

}

This loop increments the first (n-k) elements (since idx starts at 0 and goes up to n-k-1) until sAll is 0.
